newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: No trade in Australia's SFE wheat futures.
newsitem.headline: No trade in Australia's SFE wheat futures.

text.p: Sydney Futures Exchange wheat futures failed to trade on Thursday with traders standing aside to await direction from Chicago.
"People are looking at Chicago and asking 'is it going to bottom or isn't it going to bottom?'," Brendan Hillary of ANZ Futures Ltd said.

He said market attention was particularly focussed on the assessment expected from the current Wheat Quality Council tours of Kansas wheat crops affected by the mid-April freeze and its likely impact on Chicago wheat futures.
"People are waiting for fresh information," he said.
